    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n👋 \n\ni was trying to build Neovim from source but i keep on getting the same build error, apparently no matter what i try...\n\nthe error is always the same, when trying to to generate `auto/lua/vim_module.generated.h` i believe\n```\nsrc/gen/gen_char_blob.lua:51: bad argument #1 to 'format' (number expected, got string)\nstack traceback:\n        [C]: in function 'format'\n        src/gen/gen_char_blob.lua:51: in main chunk\n        [C]: at 0x5d3d742b73e0\n```\n\n> - i did check all the links above and could not find anything mentioning the error nor the involved file\n> - i did run the commands in `BUILD.md`, i.e. `sudo apt-get install ninja-build gettext cmake curl build-essential`\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nthe steps are quite straighforward\n```bash\nmake distclean\nmake\n```\n\n> i tried with the following configurations, from the source of neovim\n> - `git checkout stable && make distclean && make`\n> - `git checkout master && make distclean && make`\n> - `git checkout 68eece8b849da73bb9c93dabd6403ed0fb2f4174 && make distclean && make` (the version i currently have)\n> - `git checkout v0.12.0 && make distclean && make` (the closest tag to my current version)\n> \n> i also tried with `make CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release`, `make CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug` and `make CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=RelWithDebInfo` but none of them worked\n\n### Expected behavior\n\ni swear i did the same thing already in the past, so i guess i am expecting `make` to build Neovim :)\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nxxx\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nxxx\n\n### Operating system/version\n\n`Linux port-stevan-l 6.8.0-107-generic #107~22.04.1-Ubuntu SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Wed Mar 18 23:40:43 UTC  x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux`\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nxxx\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxxx\n\n### Installation\n\ni just cloned from GitHub",
