            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> That's very unusual.\n>\nyes, i'm pretty confused by all this !\n\n> Try adding some lines here to see what's going on (PR welcome too, to catch this in the future):\n> \nso i am on 68eece8b84 because i know for sure i was able to build this in the past as i'm running it right now.\n\ni just applied the following patch, adding some prints around line 51 and around the `if` block\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/gen/gen_char_blob.lua b/src/gen/gen_char_blob.lua\nindex c40e0d6e82..8245725d3d 100644\n--- a/src/gen/gen_char_blob.lua\n+++ b/src/gen/gen_char_blob.lua\n@@ -43,16 +43,20 @@ for argi = 2, #arg, 2 do\n   local varname = string.gsub(modname, '%.', '_dot_') .. '_module'\n   target:write(('static const uint8_t %s[] = {\\n'):format(varname))\n \n+  print(\"=== 0\")\n   local output\n   if options.c then\n     local luac = os.getenv('LUAC_PRG')\n     if luac and luac ~= '' then\n+      print(\"=== 1\")\n       output = io.popen(luac:format(source_file), 'r'):read('*a')\n+      print(\"=== 2\")\n     elseif warn_on_missing_compiler then\n       print('LUAC_PRG is missing, embedding raw source')\n       warn_on_missing_compiler = false\n     end\n   end\n+  print(\"=== 3\")\n \n   if not output then\n     local source = io.open(source_file, 'r')\n```\nand, when running `make distclean` and `make CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release`, i see 0 and 1, but not 2 nor 3.\n\n**==>** this is the first time i look at the source code of Neovim, i would be happy to help more !\n\n> p.s. the default `make` builds a DEBUG build, don't use that for normal usage. https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/BUILD.md#building\n>\nyup, that's why i tried the other build methods, i would like `CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release`\n",
