            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "That makes sense. Ideally we should escape the `_CHECK_LUAC_PRG` / `LUA_PRG` values when building the `LUAC_PRG` string:\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/2287c374863988c99b4f20ee9aa0b3771527d8ed/CMakeLists.txt#L214-L223\n\nthere is another risk in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/2287c374863988c99b4f20ee9aa0b3771527d8ed/src/gen/gen_char_blob.lua#L51\n\nwhich is that the command will be broken if `source_file` has spaces in its path.\n\nLet's keep this open for tracking, though I don't plan to work on it personally but hope someone will :)\n",
