            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "i think i was able to fix this with the following patch\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/gen/gen_char_blob.lua b/src/gen/gen_char_blob.lua\nindex c40e0d6e82..4fcc782852 100644\n--- a/src/gen/gen_char_blob.lua\n+++ b/src/gen/gen_char_blob.lua\n@@ -46,6 +46,8 @@ for argi = 2, #arg, 2 do\n   local output\n   if options.c then\n     local luac = os.getenv('LUAC_PRG')\n+    luac = string.gsub(luac, \"%%\", \"%%%%\") -- escape %\n+    luac = string.gsub(luac, \"%%%%s \", \"%%s \") -- restore the %s argument\n     if luac and luac ~= '' then\n       output = io.popen(luac:format(source_file), 'r'):read('*a')\n     elseif warn_on_missing_compiler then\n```\n\nit builds to completion !\n\nthe only issue is, when i then run `./build/bin/nvim`, it gives me an error `E5113: Lua chunk: vim/_init_packages.lua:0: module 'vim.pack' not found` :/",
