        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@justinmk the issue i have is that `LUAC_PRG` is not just the command itself but rather the command plus its arguments in a single string...\n\ni'm not sure this solution is robust against paths to `luac` containing spaces and `%s` but i think this sould take care of my current issue\n```diff\ndiff --git a/src/gen/gen_char_blob.lua b/src/gen/gen_char_blob.lua\nindex c40e0d6e82..570422be1e 100644\n--- a/src/gen/gen_char_blob.lua\n+++ b/src/gen/gen_char_blob.lua\n@@ -46,6 +46,9 @@ for argi = 2, #arg, 2 do\n   local output\n   if options.c then\n     local luac = os.getenv('LUAC_PRG')\n+    luac = string.gsub(luac, \"%%\", \"%%%%\") -- escape %\n+    luac = string.gsub(luac, \"%%%%s \", \"%%s \") --| restore the %s argument\n+    luac = string.gsub(luac, \" %%%%s\", \" %%s\") --|\n     if luac and luac ~= '' then\n       output = io.popen(luac:format(source_file), 'r'):read('*a')\n     elseif warn_on_missing_compiler then\n```\n\ni was thinking of splitting the `luac` variable by space to only replace in the first token, but this won't solve the issue of paths containing spaces...\n\nwould you like me to open a PR with the patch above as a first step ?",
